## BP-CLI-01: Validate command

test TC-CLI-01-01 "Validate a clean model prints valid and exits zero"
  verifies: BP-CLI-01
  given: a model directory whose parsed SystemModel has no
         validation errors
  when: the user runs "blueprint validate <dir>"
  expect: stdout includes the word "valid", exit code is 0

test TC-CLI-01-02 "Validate a broken model prints errors and exits non-zero"
  verifies: BP-CLI-01
  given: a model directory whose parsed SystemModel produces
         at least one validation error
  when: the user runs "blueprint validate <dir>"
  expect: stdout or stderr includes the error message with
          file path and line number, exit code is non-zero

test TC-CLI-01-03 "Parse error prints file path and exits non-zero"
  verifies: BP-CLI-01
  given: a model directory where one .req file has a syntax error
  when: the user runs "blueprint validate <dir>"
  expect: output contains the offending file name and exit code
          is non-zero

## BP-CLI-02: Assemble command

test TC-CLI-02-01 "Assemble writes one JSON file per component"
  verifies: BP-CLI-02
  given: a valid model directory with three components and an
         empty output directory
  when: the user runs "blueprint assemble <sys-dir> <out-dir>"
  expect: three <component-id>.json files exist under the
          output directory, exit code is 0

test TC-CLI-02-02 "Assemble refuses when model is invalid"
  verifies: BP-CLI-02
  given: a model directory whose parsed SystemModel has a
         validation error
  when: the user runs "blueprint assemble <sys-dir> <out-dir>"
  expect: no files are written, exit code is non-zero,
          stderr mentions the validation error

## BP-CLI-07: Serve command

test TC-CLI-07-01 "Serve validates port argument"
  verifies: BP-CLI-07
  given: an invocation "blueprint serve --port not-a-number"
  expect: exit code is non-zero and stderr mentions "port"

test TC-CLI-07-02 "Serve rejects missing port value"
  verifies: BP-CLI-07
  given: an invocation "blueprint serve --port" with no value
  expect: exit code is non-zero

## BP-CLI-03: Sync command

test TC-CLI-03-01 "Sync with no baseline writes everything and saves baseline"
  verifies: BP-CLI-03
  given: a valid model directory and no existing baseline file
  when: the user runs "blueprint sync <sys-dir> <out-dir>" from
        a working directory with no .blueprint/baseline.json
  expect: AgentContext files are written for every component,
          a .blueprint/baseline.json is created, and exit
          code is 0

test TC-CLI-03-02 "Sync with unchanged model writes nothing new"
  verifies: BP-CLI-03
  given: a baseline that matches the current model
  when: the user runs "blueprint sync" again
  expect: stdout reports no changes, no files are regenerated,
          exit code is 0

test TC-CLI-03-03 "Sync regenerates only affected components"
  verifies: BP-CLI-03
  given: a baseline and a current model where only one component
         has changed
  when: the user runs "blueprint sync <sys-dir> <out-dir>"
  expect: only the affected component's AgentContext is written
          and the baseline is updated, exit code is 0

## BP-CLI-04: Trace command

test TC-CLI-04-01 "Forward trace prints satisfied_by and verified_by"
  verifies: BP-CLI-04
  given: a model directory where REQ-001 is satisfied by COMP-A
         and verified by TC-001
  when: the user runs "blueprint trace REQ-001 <dir>"
  expect: stdout contains "COMP-A" and "TC-001", exit code is 0

test TC-CLI-04-02 "Backward trace from test spec lists requirements"
  verifies: BP-CLI-04
  given: a model directory where TC-001 verifies REQ-001
  when: the user runs "blueprint trace TC-001 backward <dir>"
  expect: stdout contains "REQ-001", exit code is 0

test TC-CLI-04-03 "Trace of unknown id exits non-zero"
  verifies: BP-CLI-04
  given: a model directory with no element id "REQ-NONE"
  when: the user runs "blueprint trace REQ-NONE <dir>"
  expect: exit code is non-zero

## BP-CLI-05: Verify command

test TC-CLI-05-01 "Verify prints coverage percentage"
  verifies: BP-CLI-05
  given: a model directory with at least one verified requirement
  when: the user runs "blueprint verify <dir>"
  expect: stdout contains a percentage and the coverage
          summary line

test TC-CLI-05-02 "Verify lists uncovered requirements"
  verifies: BP-CLI-05
  given: a model directory with one requirement and no test specs
  when: the user runs "blueprint verify <dir>"
  expect: stdout lists the uncovered requirement id,
          exit code is non-zero

test TC-CLI-05-03 "Verify returns zero when fully covered and allocated"
  verifies: BP-CLI-05
  given: a model where every requirement is verified and every
         system requirement is satisfied by a component
  when: the user runs "blueprint verify <dir>"
  expect: exit code is 0

## BP-CLI-06: Model directory option

test TC-CLI-06-01 "Positional directory argument is used"
  verifies: BP-CLI-06
  given: a valid model directory at path "./custom/sys"
  when: the user runs "blueprint validate ./custom/sys"
  expect: the CLI parses that directory (not the default sys/)
          and exits 0

test TC-CLI-06-02 "Default directory is sys when no argument given"
  verifies: BP-CLI-06
  given: a working directory containing a valid sys/ folder
  when: the user runs "blueprint validate" with no path
  expect: the CLI reads from "sys" relative to the working
          directory and exits 0

test TC-CLI-06-03 "Unknown subcommand prints usage and exits non-zero"
  verifies: BP-CLI-06
  given: an invocation "blueprint bogus"
  expect: stderr contains "usage" or "unknown command", exit
          code is non-zero
